Event_Notes: Total time worked in transect: 8.7 hrs.There were several issues associated with this transect. First, the azimuth was changed several times during the 2010 sampling. The azimuths for the transect were as follows: 0-20 m: 102 degrees, 20-80 m: 137 degrees, 80-100 m: 116 degrees. 100-540 m: 137 degrees, 540-600 m: 147 degrees, 600-660 m: 137 degrees, 660-800 m: 153 degrees, 800-1020: 156 degrees. Second, during the 2010 sampling, the crew recorded two 780-800 segments, resulting in the transect being 1020 meters long. These changes are noted in the segments. The number in parentheses in the segment note corresponds to what was written on the flagging at each segment end.
